The paper discusses the development of domain-independent systems for hierarchical planning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes an extension to PDDL, which is a language used in non-hierarchical planning, indicating a connection to programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL and cs.SE). The paper also discusses solving techniques and the lack of a common input language, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO).
